I am working with external servers so first I uploaded soundfiles on an external server. With the start script of game I am loading these files with
[code:1coeonlg]loadMusic (&quot;sound1&quot;,&quot;http&#58;//www&#46;test&#46;org/forest&#46;wav&quot;, &quot;&quot;)[/code:1coeonlg]

[code:1coeonlg]  &lt;function name=&quot;loadMusic&quot; parameters=&quot;id, url, url2&quot;&gt;&lt;!&#91;CDATA&#91;
	text=&quot;&lt;audio id='&quot;+ id +&quot;'&gt;&lt;source src='&quot;+url +&quot;' /&gt;&quot;
	if (LengthOf(url2)&gt;0){
		text = text + &quot;&lt;source src='&quot; + url2 +&quot;' /&gt;&quot;
	}
	text = text + &quot;&lt;/audio&gt;&quot;
	msg(text)

  &#93;&#93;&gt;&lt;/function&gt;[/code:1coeonlg]

Then I have two functions to start and stop playing the file: playMusic (&quot;sound1&quot;) and stopMusic (&quot;sound1&quot;)
[code:1coeonlg]  &lt;function name=&quot;playMusic&quot; parameters=&quot;id&quot;&gt;
    JS&#46;playMusic (id)
  &lt;/function&gt;
  &lt;function name=&quot;stopMusic&quot; parameters=&quot;id&quot;&gt;
    JS&#46;stopMusic (id)
  &lt;/function&gt;[/code:1coeonlg]

And here are the Javascript functions:
[code:1coeonlg]
function playMusic(id) {
	document&#46;getElementById(id)&#46;play();
}	

function stopMusic(id) {
	document&#46;getElementById(id)&#46;pause();
}	[/code:1coeonlg]

You can test it here with my test game: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://play.textadventures.co.uk/Play.aspx?id=ll_rm8rgtkciomchphqmyw">http://play.textadventures.co.uk/Play.a ... omchphqmyw</a><!-- m -->

